race.comment: KADDARI (8) is close to a win, running on hard to place in two of the last three. Rates clearly on top in this line-up and won't get a better chance to get off the mark. NEW ROMANCE (10) has been tested over further in the last couple and is going better than form looks. Back in trip, drawn for a soft run with a smother, and should be in the finish this time. KOVU (4) ran a great race fresh for a close-up seventh then was disappointing in the latest. Rates strongly on last third-up run though, when just missing with a close-up fourth. Fitter and can atone. EN MER (3) bombed the start fresh so forgive the run. Fitter and extra trip suits. Expected to bounce back. KOYUGA RIP (6) is a lightly raced galloper thereabouts over sharper distances. Stretched out in journey now and can improve sharply.
